caption: Couscous is an amazing authentic small restaurant.  The food is made to order and very fresh.  The Falafel and tahini were my favorite.   The fried onion and bulgur with leantils were also delicious.
The food was so yummy I forgot to take pics. Except for the location of the bathroom, the place was great. Parking could be a pain sometime. But the food is worth it. Also try the housemade lemonade.
Good portion and very delicious with the middle eastern authentic taste!
Amazing food & fast service, always a hit!
Very good vegetarian menu. Always fresh and neat.

Delicious! Fresh! Quality food!! Fast and friendly service. 10/10! A+!! Now I wish I took some pics! But we had the chicken shawarma platter, the vegetarian combo- baba ganoush, hummus, tabouli, Jerusalem salad, fried veggies, warm pita bread, dolma, falafel and rice. A little bit of everything and my tummy is satisfied and happy. Thank you Couscous!

If you are looking for good mediterranean food - Coucous is not the place. I do my best not to write bad reviews but, I don't want anyone to waste their money; there are better places to eat Mediterranean foods. I bought the chicken shawerma sandwich it was dripping in tahini sauce it did not taste good. The Faleel had an awful taste it was the worst I've ever had. The Hummus was not best but everything else I bought was not edible this was a waste of $31.78. I wouldn't eat there again, I've wondered why they don't have many customers - I got my answer today. While in this pandemic I've been trying to give restaurants business but,  I think Couscous gave me the business today.
Hours are incorrect. Here at 1145 am and they are closed without a light on.  Update went inside to eat for dinner and smelled like raw sewage inside! Plumbing inside building needs to be fixed asap
Very fresh food and great service!
The spot is fantastic and spacious, the food was enchanting and the prices were very reasonable. rapidly, productive service and very friendly staff. Will definitely recommend this place.
Authentic Middle Eastern food, with a Palestinian zest. The owner and his family were very welcoming and the food was awesome!
Delicious food.  Felt like eating at home. The customer service is friwndly with that old world feel (to the point). Will definitely return! Thanks
The atmosphere was calm and authentic.  We enjoyed the meal.  The food was above average quality and portions were above average size.  Prices were reasonable.  In short, we would eat here again.
Homemade excellent quuality.
Yummy Moroccan.
What a hole in the wall - great owners, great food. Worth every penny and more
One of the best Mediterranean places around. Lamb, chicken, and falafel are super good.
The food was AMAZING!! came in not knowing what to expect but was better then expected...will definitely be coming back more often.
Great food!
Millons 🌟 Ma Sha Allah, very good good. Must visit highly recommend.
Great food, reasonable prices, welcoming staff.
I live this place food As North African, I can tell you that the couscous here is very authentic. It's Tunisian version

Walked in the place without prior knowledge of the place or its services. The only thing that got our attention is its name and type of food it serve, Mediterranean. Simple place, but amazing attitude of the owner with most friendliest services. The food was excellent, was made exactly to our liking. It was one of our most enjoyably meals in Chicago so far. Tank you Jawad for your services.
Bomb and authentic mediterranean for damn good prices

This is literally my favorite restaurant on Taylor. I can't get enough of their chicken shawarma pita sandwich! Truly delicious. Jowal is also very kind and would sneak me some samples of his freshly made falafels in my orders! It seems as if he does all the cooking and work himself!  I come back every week. :)

This is a favorite of mine, right down from Rush.  Jowal the store owner is great, he is acommodating.  This is a  great place for sit down.  Ive never seen anyone else in the back, and I feel that he runs this place solo.  Being that, it is great.  So dont be in a rush, immerse yourself in the food and culture.  Take the time to speak and get transported to a different place.

Food items were missing that were paid for.  Took 25 minutes past the pickup time, we stood and waited.  Items were swapped for things we didn't order.  The packaging was horrible.  Will never return.  Doubt my roommate will either.
Couscous was exceptional. The food was awesome.
Great home cooked food

Okay food for the price and quick, but you get what you pay for. Our server literally brought us our food, asked if we wanted plates, then walked out the front door and never came back. We grabbed some bowls from the buffet in the back instead but that was sort of weird. You're probably better off getting take out.

(Translated by Google) Rich, delicious, the place very quiet, comfortable, and the service very good, and a very good price. I loved.  (Original) Rico, delicioso, el lugar muy tranquilo, cómodo, y el sevicio muy bueno,  y un muy buen precio. Me encantó.
Meh
Great place for delicious Mediterranean food. The staff was very sociable and kind.
Great food. Reasonable price. Great Costumer service.
They shouldn't call it couscous because their couscous is so bad
Not a good couscous
Chicken shawarma was delicious. Lemonade is freshly made and was hella delicious too. I recommend this restaurant!
Very salty beef. I couldn’t eat.
Good food
Great food. Wonderful owners.
Delicious hummus with warm pita bread. The lamb shwarama was tender and the rice was sublime!

I have eaten here for years, although it was some years ago. I revisited few years ago and the food was the same and just great. I hope its owned by the same family. Their tea is good, the owner makes the falafel fresh and they taste great. The hummus is good. Anything on the menu here is great. Their baklava is amazing, I haven't had that good a baklava since!
Just bad

I will say that the food here was fresh and delicious! Although there was 1 elder man doing all the work but he managed to serve myself,my daughter and 6 year old granddaughter. He was very kind and timely with our service. The space is small and could use a new paint  job and a little TLC . A good quick stop for good Mediterranean dishes.
Very good food cozy place
Owners are very friendly and considerate!! Made a large order of falafels for us in a short amount of time. My group definitely enjoyed!
Food is delicious quantity is good. Place could be more neat.
Loved it beautiful place and the food is amazing!
Salad was fresh and the couscous is ok..
Great food. Great price. Great service.
Very nice price and delicious food!

A wide choice of Mediterranean dishes and really affordable, surprisingly affordable for Taylor Street. It's not a trendy restaurant but it has AMAZING food, I wish I could give it ten stars. It is family owned and operated and the family is really nice, friendly and helpful.
Delicious food Everytime
Loved this place! My friend is vegan, I am very much not. Plenty of stuff for both of us and we were thrilled with what we got. Really neat place, will 100% be back.
One of he best Tunisian couscous I had. Variety of food and dishes, friendly staff, good prices! I highly recommend this place.
Owner is awkward if not somewhat rude
Good food at the right prices.
Duh! Great azz food and great service. Oh yea and plenty of food at that. Put you in that quick mid-afternoon nap mode.
Great Mediterranean Food.

We had an all you can eat vegan meet up dinner and the dishes were delicious, esp. the okra. There were 2 rice dishes and couscous with lots of veggies. The spinach was a bit watery but it's ok coz it has lots of mushroom in it. The falafel were good, not greasy or oily like other places. And the fruit salad was very fruity with a slight hint of rose water.  I will definitely come back and recommend it to others.
Mediterranean restaurant on Taylor street.  Vegetarian friendly menu. Food is plentiful but have had better food elsewhere.
Chicken Tikka extra spicy 😋

The veggie plate is sooo rich I love it. It’s got at least 10 different food items. Hot and cold with both Hummus and Baba Ganoush. The falafel is hot and made there. Would come back again for the veggie plate.
When I feel homesick I jest go to couscous, the owner is nice person. I like the rice there.

Ordered the Chicken Shawarma to go from an extremely surly person that I believe was the owner.  I also asked for extra garlic sauce and bread when I ordered, which I have been more than happy to pay for at other establishments in the past.  After an extremely long wait (during which I was told it took so long because he cooks each order as it is made), I finally got my food.  What I got was flavorless meat (besides a charred taste on some of the meat), extremely runny garlic sauce, and no bread.  I"ve had Shawarma from quite a number of places, and never has it been this bad, nor the service this terrible.

Worst experience had ever been called them asking for something they said yes it is available i drive all the way once gets there they said no we don't have what you asking for it s ok Ordered some thing else awful food derty kitchen only one guy in the restaurant doing everything cooking serving and bla bla bla bla nothing more to say about this place A slice of cheese pizza way better

Bad food, had an upset stomach after eating it. Ordered a  falafel sandwich which had some tahini type of sauce in it, the sauce was super tangy I could barely manage to finish my food. Not going back.
Walked into this place and walked right back out immediately.  Terrible odor that smell like sewage back-up or something.

Best falafel in the city.  Nearly everything is made fresh and each dish is perfectly spiced.    The gentleman that runs this restaurant is very kind and generous.  You won't find great Mediterranean food like this anywhere else in the city at such a bargain.
I've ordered from here several times. The food is generally decent, though I have had a subpar meal here on occasion. The service is fairly poor and has made me decide to stop ordering there.
Horrible experience. I order a lamb chop meal and there was a dead insect in my food and the owner decided to do nothing and was very rude!!!
Very good food with appropriate meal sizes!
Definitely the best Kibbe and grape leaves I've had in America. A must go restaurant
Have never been disappointed with the food here. It's always fantastic and the prices are very reasonable for Taylor Street. Try the lamb kallaya!

Very good Mediterranean food. Quality falafels and grape leaves. The tabbouleh was tasty too. There is apparently a lunch buffett that I would like to try. You can tell the food is legit because there is a TV playing programs in Arabic.
Always love, love the food. The owner is super nice as well. I'd recommend it for anyone. Love the breek especially.
its one of the best Couscous restaurant in Chicago
Amazing place !! Lovely people serving, and the food, fresh and totally pleasing !! Super satisfied with the place ! Sorry couldn't take a picture as i was busy hogging !

Came here as a group of 7 we literally ordered half the menu and everything tasted so good.  Chicken shawarma sandwich was delicious, chicken tikka had so much flavor to it also the lentil soup on point.  We also got several vegetarian dishes that were delicious.  If you want delicious home cooked meals go here!
Great food, very cheap, always leave satisfied, even on some nights when the owner is the only worker!
Chicken Tikka, chicken shwarama and falafel sandwiches are my fave. I would give it more stars if I could. The owner is super nice and works hard to make sure his customers enjoy their food.
Lovely atmosphere and exceptional food
Lamb Kabob sandwich was great.

Best falafel sandwich you'll find between Chicago & Dallas. Trust me. Go lettuce, tomatoes & onions (no cucumbers) w/tahini on the side. The owner loves all of his customers & treats regulars like family.
Quick and friendly service. Good shawarma at a great price! The baba ganooj was also excellent.

The food is good. But every single time I went there, some problem happened. Once I ordered something, they gave me something else. Another day, I was billed 45$ more than what it actually was. The food is good. But I am seriously scared about going there.
Great food. Owner is short but service is acceptable.

The first time we went it was good food with service poor. However,  the second time the food was unfortunately poor. The falafel were cold, kabobs were very tough. Kallaya was good. Service was awful. I got my own water and plates. Unfortunate part was when I brought the food to the owner,  he just walked away. It was unfortunate.  Not going back
Excellent tasty food...not very expensive either . They started lunch buffet now. $8.95.

The food is succulent, mouth-watering, and aromatic.  The decor went under a wonderful renovation, and looks very nice (it looked nice before, too)  And the management has always been very helpful and friendly to our family! We'll always come back!
excellent mediterranean food
